metadata:
  section_id: 31
  section_name: Chapter 31
  hadith_first: 201
  hadith_last: 210

hadiths[10]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
201,“The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) drank from  Zamzam while standing.”,,,48916,"Ibn 'Abbas said (may Allah be well pleased with him and his father):",Chapter 31
202,"""I saw Allah's Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) drink while both standing and sitting.”",,,48917,"'Amr ibn Shu'aib reports on the authority of his father that his grandfather said:",Chapter 31
203,"""I gave Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) Zamzam water, and he drank it standing up.”",,,48918,"Ibn 'Abbas said (may Allah be well pleased with him and his father):",Chapter 31
204,"'This is the minor ritual ablution of someone who has not excreted any substance that would render him ritually impure. I saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) act in this manner'.""",,,48919,"An-Nazzal ibn Sabra said;\n""Ali (may Allah be well pleased with him) brought a jug of water, while he was in ar-Rahba, after which he dipped out a handful, washed his hands, rinsed his mouth, snuffed up his nostrils, and wiped his face, his forearms and his head. Then he drank from it while standing. Then he said:",Chapter 31
205,"""The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to breathe into the vessel three times when he drank, and he would say: 'It is more wholesome and more thirst-quenching!’”",,,48920,"Anas ibn Malik said (may Allah be well pleased with him):",Chapter 31
206,"""When the Prophet drank (Allah bless him and give him peace), he used to take two breaths.”",,,48921,"Ibn 'Abbas said (may Allah be well pleased with him and his father):",Chapter 31
207,"""The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) entered my presence, then he drank from a suspended waterskin while standing, so I reached up to its mouth and cut it loose.”",,,48922,"'Abd ar-Rahman ibn Abi 'Amra said that his grandmother Kabsha said:",Chapter 31
208,"“Anas ibn Malik used to breathe into the vessel three times, and Anas ibn Malik maintained that the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) likewise used to breathe into the vessel three times.”",,,48923,"Thumama ibn 'Abdi’llah said:",Chapter 31
209,"""The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) entered the presence of Umm Sulaim, and a waterskin was suspended there, so he drank from the mouth of the waterskin while standing. Umm Sulaim therefore reached up to the head of the waterskin and cut it loose.”",,,48924,"Anas ibn Malik said:",Chapter 31
210,“The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to drink while standing.”,,,48925,"'A’isha bint Sa'd ibn Abi Waqqas reported that her father said:",Chapter 31
